Stocks - https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=fn3y1hNVgA4
Stocks are pieces / shares of ownership of a company. Each share worth a certain amount based on what company is worth. 

Bonds - https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ftsNgtx2haY
Bond is a contract where a company or governmane borrows money from a person for a period of time in return of internest payments. Its like a company or government taking out a loan directly from an individual.
Coupon bonds (Companies)- Periodic payments (interest) till the period decided and in the end return the capital amount.
Zero Coupon bonds (Govt.) - Capital + Interest paid directly at the end of tenure.
Bonds do not lent piece (share) of company, just lend money like banks do.
